TY  - JOUR
T1  - Specification testing when score test statistics are identically zero
AU  - Lee, Lung-Fei
AU  - Chesher, Andrew
JO  - Journal of Econometrics
VL  - 31
IS  - 2
SP  - 121
EP  - 149
PY  - 1986
DA  - 1986/03/01/
SN  - 0304-4076
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-4076(86)90045-X
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/030440768690045X
AB  - We investigate the problem of specification testing when the score vector evaluated at the restricted MLE is identically zero. Several econometric examples are provided. A general test procedure which generalizes the geometric principle of the score test is proposed. The Wald and the likelihood ratio tests are also analyzed. Even under such irregularities, the usual asymptotic distribution of the likelihood ratio statistics is still valid. However, the Wald-type statistics need to be modified. The generalized score, the likelihood ratio and the modified Wald tests are shown to be asymptotically equivalent. The asymptotic efficiency of the tests is derived.
